  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6763 sitting right in the thick negative gamma zone (-65.7B at 6750), dealers are forced to buy this rally as they're short gamma and getting squeezed. The breakout regime with massive negative GEX (-143B total) means dealer hedging will amplify moves in both directions, creating a volatile trending environment rather than mean reversion. Key level is the 6800 strike with +34B positive gamma where dealers flip to selling pressure - expect fierce resistance there, while any dip toward 6750-6755 should see aggressive dealer buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect explosive moves with dealers amplifying both rallies toward 6800 and any potential selloffs.",
